DSP.title1: Microphone Input to Ambisonic Conversion#[ #] Module(MIC2AMB)

MODULE.name: MODULE_ID_MIC2AMB
MODULE.description:
Microphone Input to Ambisonic Conversion Module.
This module supports the#[ #] following parameter IDs:
- #PARAM_ID_MIC2AMB_ENABLE
- #PARAM_ID_MIC2AMB_CONFIG
- #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_ENABLE
- #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_LIB_VERSION

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: ambisonic_order
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the ambisonic order of output data

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: norm_type
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the normalization type of output data

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: channel_order_type
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the channel order type of output data

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: noise_order
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the order of noise gain

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: dim_inp_ch
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies number of microphone input channels in MIC2AMB processing

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: noise_gain_buf
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Array of noise gain 2D buffer of dimension [x][y] where x=(noise_order +1), y=(fft_size/2+1); array contains linear gain of int32_t#[ #] data(one word)in Q28, Size of array is dynamic and it's equivalent to x*y words

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: mixing_gain_buf
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Array of mixing gain matrix 3D buffer of dimension [x][y][z] where x=compensation_order, y= (ambisonic_order+1)^2, z=dim_inp_ch; Array#[ #] contains linear gain of int32_t data(one word) in Q28, Size of array is dynamic and it's equivalent to x*y*z words

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: filter_coeffs_buf
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Array of filter coefficients 3D buffer of dimension [x][y][z] where x=compensation_order, y= (ambisonic_order+1)^2, z=(fft_size/2+1);#[ #] Array contains complex filter coefficients of cint2x32(int64_t)in Q28, Size of array is dynamic and it's equivalent to 2*x*y*z words
